Feature: a BC's git and gh operations authenticate through the agent-vault GitHub service, not a mounted gitconfig or gh token

  The NEW capability under the locked scope decision (lead-v4ih, dave 2026-06-09):
  add a GitHub credential service to the agent-vault broker so that GitHub auth is
  brokered exactly as Claude OAuth is, eliminating the last host-filesystem credential
  coupling (~/.config/gh, ~/.gitconfig). A BC agent's authenticated GitHub operation
  (e.g. bd dolt push to a private beads remote, or a gh API call) succeeds because the
  broker substitutes the stored GitHub credential on the outbound request — the
  container itself carries no GitHub token. The kill-line: an authenticated GitHub
  operation succeeds from inside the container with NO gh/gitconfig credential mounted.
  @scenario_hash:df9bce3b6a73c592
  Scenario: an authenticated GitHub operation from inside the container succeeds via the broker with no mounted GitHub credential
    Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
    And an agent-vault broker with a GitHub credential service is running on the shopsystem network and is reachable
    And the container "bc-shopsystem-messaging" is running with no host gh or gitconfig credential mounted
    When an authenticated GitHub operation is run from inside the container through the agent-vault broker
    Then the operation completes successfully against GitHub
    And no GitHub token value is present in the container's environment or filesystem

  # RETIRED (ADR-028 D3, lead-4mv3): @scenario_hash:f23dfbe84c899968 ("the broker
  # substitutes the GitHub credential on the outbound request rather than the
  # container holding it") was tautological/unfalsifiable on the launcher boundary
  # (the launcher wires the proxy; it does not perform the substitution and cannot
  # observe the broker's upstream request — ADR-028 finding 4). Its intent is
  # RELOCATED to the lead-owned integration surface as SB-2's broker arm:
  # features/agent-vault-broker/04-broker-substitutes-github-credential-on-outbound-request.gherkin
  # (@scenario_hash:1b077fab23d3baaa), exercised against the real compose-stood broker.
  # The companion 97734ca69a510e37 (end-to-end success the launcher participates in)
  # STAYS on @bc:shopsystem-bc-launcher above. Any future re-dispatch touching this
  # feature must carry an explicit @scenario_hash:f23dfbe84c899968 retirement instruction.
